## Developer Guide

If you are new to using `nbdev` here are some useful pointers to get you
started.

### Install nebari_dia_adx in Development mode

``` sh
# make sure nebari_dia_adx package is installed in development mode
$ pip install -e .

# make changes under nbs/ directory
# ...

# compile to have changes apply to nebari_dia_adx
$ nbdev_prepare
```

## Usage

### Installation

Install latest from the GitHub
[repository](https://github.com/equinor/nebari-dia-adx):

``` sh
$ pip install git+https://github.com/equinor/nebari-dia-adx.git
```

or from [conda](https://anaconda.org/equinor/nebari-dia-adx)

``` sh
$ conda install -c equinor nebari_dia_adx
```

or from [pypi](https://pypi.org/project/nebari-dia-adx/)

``` sh
$ pip install nebari_dia_adx
```

### Documentation

Documentation can be found hosted on this GitHub
[repository](https://github.com/equinor/nebari-dia-adx)’s
[pages](https://equinor.github.io/nebari-dia-adx/). Additionally you can
find package manager specific guidelines on
[conda](https://anaconda.org/equinor/nebari-dia-adx) and
[pypi](https://pypi.org/project/nebari-dia-adx/) respectively.
